text: Does anyone else follow this guy's custom set?
I love a few of his mechanics. Namely Upload and Arm.
Oh! I’ve seen this before! It’s really cool!
Right?
I've seen it before. Don't follow it though. Knowing that the WotC staff can't take inspiration from unsolicited ideas kinda kills my interest in custom-designs.
Plus the off chance that WotC designs something and a guy gets fussy because they “stole his design”.

My gripe tends to be when amateur designers design things to prove how clever they are, rather than designing things that will allow others a fun gameplay experience. There's a lot of 'look at me and my ideas' in those threads.

No shade to the thing linked above, I haven't looked through it. I'm just pontificating on a tendency that I do see an unhappy amount of the time

Or the tendency to design the commander they want that will never happen, yet the response is “omg what a great commander! I dig @wizards would print this!”

Well now you just made sure it never would be....

What do you mean they can't print my three-mana 5/5 Boros commander that draws me cards whenever I hit someone? Breaks color pie, what's that? I don't care about the color pie, Chaos Warp and Beast Within are my favorite cards ever
What do you mean Ezuri is a color pie break...
Don't get Sassy Joey started
after about the fourth rant I felt like joey was right
It’s like a summoning ritual
I'm just saying that game design is about other people, not about ego
but after the sixth, I was on the page of "I want to troll joey more now"
Ezuri, Ezuri, bring out Sassy Joey....
Did you know that if you turn off the lights and say "ezuri" three times in a mirror, Sassy Joey will appear to haunt and rant at you for the rest of your life?
Hahaha my point exactly
I get what Joey's saying about ideas to show you're clever, but I still love Time Spiral, which is entirely a set about showing off how clever you are

I used to hang out in those card design circles. My eyes would flash white with rage whenever anyone broke color pie. I even hosted a contest, specifying that entries had to follow it. Only a few people listened.
New Aurelia is like they listened to Joey about new Ezuri, and decided to make a shitty version of it just to spite him.
Lots of people were pissed they didn't win. I ended up explaining to someone how an unblockable green creature wasn't okay
